description.text: The mathematical models in present-day science and engineering almost always have multiple underlying variables, leading to PDEs that are multidimensional. In our research, we are actively involved in four application areas: financial mathematics, physics, chemistry and biology. In general, solutions to PDEs from applications cannot be expressed in closed analytic form. Accordingly, one resorts to numerical schemes for their approximate solution. The development, analysis and application of such schemes takes a central place in numerical mathematics.

title.text: Master of Science in Civil Engineering

description.text: The master's programme in Civil Engineering focuses on the study and design of buildings and structures (roads, bridges, hydraulic structures, high-rise and industrial buildings) and aims for the formation of civil engineers who can perform at a high level in an international industrial and social environment. The programme concentrates on the thorough development of the conception and design capability, with the added objective of a job in research and development. Thus lies in the core curriculum of training a pronounced emphasis on the computational aspects of buildings and infrastructure. By means of elective courses, students can select additional aspects of the field corresponding to the personal aptitude and interests. These elective courses also aim to broaden the training programme.

The university can allow students who have completed a professional programme to also enrol graduate university programmes, but they are allowed to set special requirements in these cases. El requisito mínimo de formación para matricularse en programas profesionales de postgrado es haber completado un programa universitario de grado o un programa profesional (primer ciclo).

prefLabel.text: Master of Science in Civil Engineering

description.text:
After completing the study programme the student acquires the main competences: - To formulate equations of mathematical physics for engineering problems, and to solve them analytically or with numerical methods.
- To design and perform engineering calculations of all types of structures (buildings, bridges, dams, silos, tunnels, hydrotechnical structures etc.) which are composed of different structural load bearing systems and different types of material (concrete, prestressed concrete, metal, timber, stone, masonry, composite, etc.)
- To participate in the construction of different types of structures and supervise design and construction work.
- To perform numerical modelling of structures (non-linear static and dynamic analysis of structures).
- To design and perform calculation of the fire resistance of structure. - To evaluate dynamic characteristics of structures and perform calculation of structures resistant to earthquake. - To design and perform calculation of geotechnical structures. - To analyse and solve problems related to the durability of structures in different building stages: project design, construction and maintenance. - To analyse and solve problems related to the stability of structures. - To design the concrete mixture composition and its production technology. - To perform structural reliability assessment. - To evaluate production using standard indicators, make judgement on companies based on their balance sheets and assess investments. - To manage investments and business in construction sector, to organise and plan construction work, and to perform public procurement for construction work. - To knowledge and understanding that is founded upon and extends and/or enhances preceding qualification’s level, and that provides a basis or opportunity for originality in developing and/or applying ideas, often within a research context. - To apply knowledge and problem solving abilities in new environment within multidisciplinary contexts related to the field of study. - To integrate knowledge and handle complexity, and to formulate judgments with incomplete information, that include reflection on social and ethical responsibilities. - To clearly communicate own conclusions and develop learning skills for lifelong learning.

Al finalizar el programa de estudios, el estudiante adquiere las principales competencias: - Formular ecuaciones de física matemática para problemas de ingeniería, y resolverlas analíticamente o con métodos numéricos.
- Diseñar y realizar cálculos de ingeniería de todo tipo de estructuras (edificios, puentes, presas, silos, túneles, estructuras hidrotécnicas, etc.) compuestas por diferentes sistemas de carga estructural y diferentes tipos de materiales (hormigón, hormigón pretensado, metal, madera, piedra, mampostería, compuestos, etc.)

description.text: Civil engineers design, plan, and develop technical and engineering specifications for infrastructure and construction projects. They apply engineering knowledge in a vast array of projects, from the construction of infrastructure for transportation, housing projects, and luxury buildings, to the construction of natural sites. They design plans that seek to optimise materials and integrate specifications and resource allocation within the time constraints.

Los ingenieros civiles diseñan, planifican y desarrollan especificaciones técnicas y de ingeniería para proyectos de infraestructura y construcción. Aplican los conocimientos de ingeniería en una amplia gama de proyectos, desde la construcción de infraestructuras para el transporte, proyectos de viviendas y edificios de lujo, hasta la construcción de parajes naturales. Diseñan planes que buscan optimizar los materiales e integran las especificaciones y la asignación de recursos dentro de las limitaciones de tiempo.
